

HAGDAN

   hagdán: ladder, stairs

   A few pedants will argue that the proper translation for hagdanan
   (three syllables) is “staircase” — however, in common usage, even
   hagdanan is used to mean a ladder.

   Kailangan ko ng hagdanan.
   I need a ladder.

KAHULUGAN SA TAGALOG

   hagdan: akyatang baitang
